title: For Sale/Trade:  AK-47 with Dragunov Stock - 500 Rounds Ammo
location: Nippers Corner - South Nashville - Brentwood, Nashville, Tennessee
postcontent:
I have a Norinco MAK-90 Sporter AK-47 rifle that I've decided to find a new home for. I'll be including two of the polymer 30rd mags. This is a great rifle, and everything is straight on it. The finish is good but not perfect. There are some of the expected handling marks on the finish. I have installed a dragunov style stock. It has been caringly broken in just enough to operate perfectly smooth and reliably, but certainly not worn out or abused. The bolt and trigger surfaces have been polished to insure that everything travels very smoothly. The double-hook trigger on these is superb. I have no problem maintaining a 3" group at 100-150 yards with cheap Wolf ammo. I did install a new complete recoil spring assembly last month. I have/had many different AK's and the Norinco models are among my very favorite.  Unlike many other variants, the Chinese AK's haven't been imported since it was banned in 1994.  There are a lot of them out there, but it does serve to make them more desirable and collectible than many other variants.  Also, please be clear that the MAK-90 stands head and shoulders above any cheap Romanian, or  any cheap piece of junk you've ever seen from Century Arms or IO.  I also have 500 rounds of wolf non-corrosive ammo that I'll be selling separately for $250.  It is sealed in plastic and in 20ct boxes.

MAKs are better than most AKs presently on the market in the U.S. because:

1) It is not a "parts" gun. It is 100% assembled in a foreign arsenal that has been making AKs for decades. This means no canted front sights or other shoddy workmanship. 2) It has a 1.5 mm stamped receiver where most AKs have a 1 mm. This means less heat fatigue in the weapon under hard use. 3) The barrel is thicker than most AKs. How much? Not exactly sure but the difference is visible to the naked eye. 4) The chamber and barrel are chrome lined. Why would anyone want a fighting rifle with out this vital combat feature? 5) The trigger is a double hook. This means a much smoother trigger pull than a single hook. There is no trigger slap. 6) It is selling for a lot less than the fancy Vegas Arsenal with comparable quality in everything but finish and cosmetics. 7) They were imported by the hundreds of thousands. You will be able to find plenty of parts and upgrades/accessories.


**I am willing to entertain reasonable trade offers. I won't respond to "Still available ?" emails. I'll remove the listing once it sells. Please assume it is available and ask your questions or make your offers. Phone numbers are also a very good piece of info to include if you are sincerely interested.**

title: For Sale:  Watch out for scammers on Armslist...read this before you try to buy that incredible deal
postcontent:
I have noticed something recently here on Armslist that I suspect is much like the scams on Craigslist. You may have seen it before, a too good to be true deal with pictures and everything. I have seen a few assult style rifles selling for well below current market and when I check other listings by these users they end up having multiple listings in multiple states as a "private party" how is that possible? Four or five really amazing rifles selling for way below market by a private individual in four or five separate states....smells just like a Craigslist scam. So,if you are contemplating one of these amazing deals first click on the "listings by user" link and first see if they have multiple other amazing deals in different locations....if they do then I would proceed with extreme caution....even ask them how they are selling so many great guns in multiple locations. Just be careful.  I imagine these scammer will try to flag this post off so consider reposting it if you feel inclined.

As a wise person once said "if it seems too good to be true, it probably isn't"

Cheers!

title: For Sale:  Colorado Magazine info!!! Read before buying anything
postcontent:
Remember, even if this bill passes, it DOES NOT take effect until July 1st, 2013, so you have plenty of time to buy mags. And if you are in Colorado Springs, Specialty sports have them all the time (PMAGs) for $30.
Read the bill yourself:

(2) (a) "LARGE-CAPACITY MAGAZINE" MEANS A FIXED OR
 DETACHABLE MAGAZINE, BOX, DRUM, FEED STRIP, OR SIMILAR DEVICE
CAPABLE OF ACCEPTING, OR THAT CAN BE READILY CONVERTED TO
ACCEPT, MORE THAN FIFTEEN ROUNDS OF AMMUNITION OR MORE THAN
EIGHT SHOTGUN SHELLS.
(b) "LARGE-CAPACITY MAGAZINE" DOES NOT MEAN:
(I) A FEEDING DEVICE THAT HAS BEEN PERMANENTLY ALTERED SO
THAT IT CANNOT ACCOMMODATE MORE THAN FIFTEEN ROUNDS OF
AMMUNITION;
(II) AN ATTACHED TUBULAR DEVICE DESIGNED TO ACCEPT, AND
CAPABLE OF OPERATING ONLY WITH, .22 CALIBER RIMFIRE AMMUNITION;
OR
(III) A TUBULAR MAGAZINE THAT IS CONTAINED IN A
LEVER-ACTION FIREARM.

So dont pay stupid amounts for something that isn't even going to be banned. 
Now, what happens between then and now on the Federal level is a different story.
Just be wise where you spend you money. Youre going to need it.
